{
  "texts": [
    "4 The size of LLMs makes it difficult to examine their parameters directly, but several indirect strategies can be considered to enhance explainability.",
    "Shapley Additive Explanations can help quantify the contribution of various concepts or decision paths toward a given prediction.",
    "This method can, for instance, create summary plots of the most important factors leading a model to rank certain diagnoses or treatments above others.",
    "Continued efforts should be made to make these plots readily interpretable by nontechnical users.",
    "Another approach, known as prompt engineering, manipulates inputs progressively to steer models toward certain outputs, and can be used to urge models to generate intermediate steps that result in a final outcome."
  ]
}